# FILE: `player/index.html`

Create this file and paste this EXACTLY:

```html id="bd8f8s"
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />

  <meta
    name="viewport"
    content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"
  />

  <title>Pikaverse V3</title>

  <link rel="stylesheet" href="./styles.css" />
</head>

<body>
  <div id="app"></div>

  <script type="module" src="./main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

---

# WHAT THIS FILE DOES

This is the runtime mount point.

Responsibilities:

```txt id="2j9n4u"
- load styles
- provide app container
- boot main.js
```

Nothing more.

---

# IMPORTANT RULE

Keep `index.html` minimal.

Do NOT:

* hardcode gameplay UI here
* add hunt content here
* add giant layout systems here

The runtime should own rendering.

---

# WHY `type="module"` MATTERS

This enables:

```txt id="9ql1l5"
import/export architecture
```

Without bundlers.

Which is perfect for early V3 development.

---

# IMPORTANT ARCHITECTURE WIN

Notice what now exists:

```txt id="3t9l1z"
browser
↓
main.js
↓
runtime
↓
hunt data
↓
renderer
```

That is a real platform execution flow now.

